## 🎯 PRIORITY 2: TESTING STANDARDS

### 4. Test File Organization ⭐ MANDATORY

**RULE**: ALL test files MUST be organized by module in `/tests/[module]/` subdirectories

**Structure**:
```
tests/
├── ai_assistant/                     # AI Assistant module tests
│   ├── test_ai_assistant_adapter.py
│   ├── test_ai_assistant_backend.py
│   ├── test_ai_assistant_frontend_api.py
│   ├── test_ai_assistant_hana_context.py
│   ├── test_ai_assistant_hana_e2e.py
│   ├── test_ai_assistant_hana_frontend.py
│   ├── test_ai_assistant_datasource_eventbus.py
│   └── test_ai_assistant_invoice_count_hana.py
├── data_products_v2/                 # Data Products V2 module tests
│   ├── test_data_products_v2_backend.py
│   └── test_data_products_v2_frontend_api.py
├── log/                              # Log module tests
│   ├── test_log_backend.py
│   └── test_log_frontend_api.py
├── integration/                      # Integration tests (SAP AI Core, Pydantic AI)
│   ├── test_ai_core_setup.py
│   ├── test_advanced_pydantic_ai_headers.py
│   ├── test_pydantic_ai_chat_api.py
│   └── test_pydantic_ai_sap_ai_core.py
├── debug/                            # Debug/experimental tests
│   ├── test_ai_chat_debug.py
│   ├── test_conversation_context_debug.py
│   └── test_fengshui_v49.py
├── unit/                             # Unit tests (e.g., tools/fengshui)
│   └── tools/
│       └── fengshui/
│           └── test_module_federation_agent.py
├── test_smoke.py                     # Smoke tests (top-level)
├── conftest.py                       # Shared fixtures
└── README.md                         # Test documentation
```

**FORBIDDEN**:
- ❌ Creating test files in root directory (e.g., `test_*.py` in root)
- ❌ Creating test files in module directories
- ❌ Mixing unrelated tests in same subdirectory
- ✅ ALWAYS create in `/tests/[module]/` subdirectory

**AI Enforcement**:
Before creating ANY test file, AI must ask in `<thinking>`:
1. ❓ Which module does this test belong to? (ai_assistant, data_products_v2, log, etc.)
2. ❓ Is this an integration test? (→ tests/integration/)
3. ❓ Is this a debug/experimental test? (→ tests/debug/)
4. ❓ Is the path `/tests/[appropriate_subdirectory]/test_*.py`?

**If test file not in correct subdirectory**: STOP. Place in `/tests/[module]/` directory.

**Running Tests by Module**:
```bash
pytest tests/ai_assistant/ -v          # Run AI Assistant tests only
pytest tests/data_products_v2/ -v      # Run Data Products tests only
pytest tests/integration/ -v           # Run integration tests only
pytest tests/ -v                       # Run all tests
```

