### 12. Project Tracker ⭐ MANDATORY CLEANUP RULE

**PROJECT_TRACKER.md** (~150 lines):
- QUICK START (API-First workflow, key commands, documentation links)
- ACTIVE TASKS (CRITICAL, HIGH, MEDIUM, LOW priorities - only ongoing/planned work)
- VERSION HISTORY (completed phases with learnings preserved in git tags)

**Structure** (MANDATORY):
```
## 🚀 QUICK START
- Development workflow (7 steps)
- Key commands (pytest, Feng Shui, Shi Fu)
- Documentation references

## 📋 ACTIVE TASKS
### 🔴 CRITICAL (Production Blockers)
| ID | Priority | Task | Effort | Status | Completed Date | Notes |

### 🟠 HIGH (Quality & Architecture)
| ID | Priority | Task | Effort | Status | Completed Date | Notes |

### 🟢 MEDIUM (Features & Enhancements)
| ID | Task | Effort | Status | Completed Date | Dependencies | Notes |

### 🔵 LOW (Nice to Have)
| ID | Priority | Task | Effort | Status | Completed Date | Notes |

## 📚 VERSION HISTORY
### v4.2 (date) - [title]
**Completed**: [list of accomplishments]
**Key Learnings**: [8 elements: WHAT, WHY, PROBLEM, ALTERNATIVES, CONSTRAINTS, VALIDATION, WARNINGS, CONTEXT]

### Earlier Versions
[Archived references]
```

**Column Standards** (MANDATORY):
- ✅ All ACTIVE TASKS tables use consistent columns: ID, Priority, Task, Effort, Status, Completed Date, Notes
- ✅ MEDIUM table includes Dependencies column before Notes for linking related tasks
- ✅ No variation in final column naming (always "Notes", not "Recommendation")
- ✅ Completed Date field present in all priority levels for 7-day tracking

**Completed Date Field** (MANDATORY):
- ✅ Track date when task was marked complete (YYYY-MM-DD format)
- ✅ Calculate 7-day window from completion date
- ✅ Remove task from ACTIVE TASKS when: `today - completed_date >= 7 days`
- ✅ Move task to VERSION HISTORY with completion date reference
- ❌ NEVER remove tasks before 7 days have passed

**CRITICAL RULE - Remove Completed Tasks**:
- ✅ **WHEN TASK COMPLETE (7 days)**: Remove from "ACTIVE TASKS" table 7 days after completion
- ✅ Move detailed implementation notes to "VERSION HISTORY" section under appropriate version tag
- ✅ This keeps tracker lean (only active/planned work visible)
- ✅ Historical context preserved in VERSION HISTORY + git tags
- ❌ NEVER leave completed tasks in ACTIVE TASKS table beyond 7 days
- ✅ AI must proactively remove tasks when marking complete + 7 days
- ✅ Update tracker header: `**Last Updated**: YYYY-MM-DD (Brief description of latest update)`

**Tracker Maintenance**:
1. After each session: Update date and brief description in header
2. Before git commit: Verify no completed tasks in ACTIVE TASKS
3. Move task details to VERSION HISTORY: Include learnings in 8-element format
4. Git tags: Store comprehensive work package details (reference via `git show v[version]`)

